Yeah.

00:28:44.300 --> 00:28:45.880
So, a shout out is.

00:28:45.880 --> 00:28:48.840
Just lovely to work with if you haven't tried it yet.

00:28:49.140 --> 00:28:49.320
Yeah.

00:28:49.800 --> 00:28:50.240
Awesome.

00:28:50.240 --> 00:28:50.640
I like it.

00:28:51.060 --> 00:28:57.660
So, Michael Booth created a pytest-Just plugin.

00:28:57.660 --> 00:29:08.880
And it's a plugin that adds session-scoped Just fixtures to pytest so that you can test a Just file contracts directly in your test suite.

00:29:09.620 --> 00:29:18.700
So, it lets you test, like, really nice things like Just assert there exists a CI, a CI section,

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:26.720
and that CI has a test, or it depends on test, a test following the transitive dependencies of it and so on.

00:29:26.840 --> 00:29:28.620
So, anyway, I thought that was kind of cool.

00:29:28.740 --> 00:29:34.420
So, if you do stuff with Just and pytest, check out pytest-Just.

00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:35.440
Cool.

